# Release, Store, and Privacy Rules

Mythora targets iOS and Android.

Authentication may include:
- Guest
- Google Sign-In
- Apple Sign-In

Do not change auth providers without approval.

Privacy/store safety:
- keep data collection aligned with actual app behavior
- do not add tracking SDKs casually
- keep consent, ads, analytics, and ATT/GDPR implications explicit
- do not add Play Store references to App Store screenshots or iOS-only assets
- do not add App Store references to Android-only store assets
- keep children/content-rating implications in mind for monetization and ads

Release safety:
- do not bump versions blindly
- do not change bundle IDs/package names without approval
- do not change signing configs without approval
- do not deploy production Firebase changes during app release work unless requested

Before release-related changes, inspect:
- `pubspec.yaml`
- Android Gradle config
- iOS project settings
- Firebase configs
- ad/IAP setup
